At AGI Open, Studio Bureau – a concept and design agency founded by Thijs van Dalen and Frans van Ditzhuijzen – gave a talk entitled ‘Design Rotterdam’ in Walhalla Kantine.

The graphic design, spatial design and art studio works to transform cultural institutions and companies and bring about interaction with the public. 
#AGIOpen #InProgress #Rotterdam @studio.bureau

At AGI Open Rotterdam, Fedrigoni launched Arena – a new range of uncoated natural white and ivory papers. Attendees of AGI Open received paper samples of the range as well as copies of Pulp journal no. 17 (printed entirely on Arena). The paper used for all of our nine workshops – with Joost Swarte, Erik Brandt, Harmen Liemburg, Tereza Ruller, Henning Wagenbreth, Patrick Thomas, Stefan Guzy and Bjorn Weide (Zwolf), Sigrid Calon and Markus Weisbeck – was sponsored by Fedrigoni. Thank you to Fedrigoni for your continued support and sponsorship. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #fedrigoni @fedrigonipapers @fedrigoni_uk @pulpjournal_ #AGIOpen #InProgress #Rotterdam

At AGI Open, #AGI member and designer Sigrid Calon gave a talk entitled ‘Identity and In Between’ at venue Belvedere Expo Ruimte.

Sigrid feels connected to the original design aesthetics of Dutch Design: minimalistic, experimental, innovative, unconventional and with a sense of humor. Her first book To the Extend of / \ | & - led to her international breakthrough in 2012. The book and eponymous riso prints have taken her to Art Book Fairs in Milan, Basel, Los Angeles and New York, to institutes such as the MoMA, Victoria & Albert Museum, Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam and Museum Boijmans van Beuningen as well as libraries, institutes and private enthusiasts.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #sigridcalon #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @sigridcalon

Jonathan Castro is a graphic designer from Lima, Perú based in Amsterdam. Jonathan uses graphic design as a colourful depiction of a living spirit always moving in search of new possible visual futures, tools and languages. At AGI Open Rotterdam, Jonathan gave a talk entitled ‘Identity and Memory’ in the Walhalla Kantine. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @jonacthan

AGI member Patrick Thomas runs international collaborative workshops – follow @open_collab to participate and download the FREE INFO pack in his bio (version 2.0 coming soon). At AGI Open Rotterdam, Patrick ran ‘AGI Open Collab’ in the Music Factory with 25 Open attendees. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @xpatrickthomas

Amsterdam-based independent designer Tereza Ruller is an educator and the co-founder of studio The Rodina. Tereza ran a ‘Design and Screen Print’ workshop at AGI Open Rotterdam before giving a talk on the subject of ‘Culture and Social Issues’.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @therodina #TerezaRuller

At AGI Open, #AGI member and designer Paul Mijksenaar gave a talk entitled ‘Let’s Get Lost’ at venue Walhalla Theater.

Paul is a specialist in creating visual information systems such as his extensive work for Amsterdam Airport Schiphol (since 1990) and many other airports around the world, not to mention railways, metro, hospitals and museums. 
#AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @paulmijksenaar_works

Luna Maurer is an interaction and media design artist; together with Roel Wouters she is head of the Amsterdam-based studio Moniker. Moniker explores characteristics of technology, and how it influences our daily lives. They are experts in participatory projects and have a warm heart for the web, film and performances. At AGI Open, Luna gave a talk entitled ‘Culture and Social Issues’ at Walhalla Kantine. 
#AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress #LunaMaurer @studiomoniker

At AGI Open, #AGI member Joost Grootens gave a talk entitled ‘Mapping in the digital age’ at venue Zaak Acht. 
Joost leads the masters programme Information Design at Design Academy Eindhoven, and is a mapping tutor at KADK Copenhagen and Professor Information Architecture at ISIA Urbino. Since 2015 Joost Grootens is PhD candidate at Leiden University.

#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #joostgrootens @studiojoostgrootens #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress

Pentagram Partner, graphic designer and AGI member Paula Scher gave a talk entitled ‘How to be Paula Scher’ at Walhalla Theater for AGI Open Rotterdam on 24 September 2019. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress #PaulaScher @pentagramdesign

Artist and illustrator Harmen Liemburg originally trained as a cartographer; he later enrolled at Amsterdam’s Gerrit Rietveld Academy. He became part of a new generation of Dutch designers. In line with his obsession with screen printing, Harmen ran a ‘Design and Screen Print’ workshop at AGI Open Rotterdam. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #HarmenLiemburg @harmenliemburg #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress

Matthias Kreutzer and Jens Schildt founded graphic and type design studio Our Polite Society, based in Amsterdam and Stockholm, in 2008.
Together they design books, magazines, posters, exhibitions, signage systems, record sleeves, screens and typefaces. Among others, Our Polite Society have produced works for Bauhaus Dessau, the University of Stockholm, the Sandberg Instituut Amsterdam, the New Institute Rotterdam, Malmö Konsthall, and Internationale Bauausstellung (IBA). At AGI Open, Matthias and Jens gave a talk entitled ‘Culture & Social Issues’; they spoke in Zaak Acht.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #MatthiasKreutzer #JensSchildt #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @our_polite_society

Illustrator, graphic designer and AGI member Pooroni Rhee is interested in visual narrative and storytelling, studying the relationship between design/art, ambiguity/clarity and verbal/pictorial. At AGI Open Rotterdam, Pooroni talked about ‘Image of Illustration’ in Walhalla WC.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #pooronirhee #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @pooroni

Pentagram Partner, graphic designer, film-maker and AGI member Marina Willer spoke at Walhalla Theater at AGI Open Rotterdam before screening her documentary film Red Trees, which premiered at the 2017 Cannes Film Festival. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress #MarinaWiller @marina_willer

AGI member Jon Sueda established design studio Stripe in 2004, which specializes in print and exhibition design for art and culture. In 2007, Sueda relocated to the San Francisco area where he served as Director of Design at the CCA Wattis Institute for Contemporary Arts for seven years. He is currently the Chair of the MFA Design program at California College of the Arts. At AGI Open, Jon’s talk was entitled ‘Designers Publish’; he spoke in Walhalla FC.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #JonSueda #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @jsueda

AGI member Hansje van Halem established her own studio in Amsterdam in 2003. She is passionate about typography, book design and print in all its forms.

At AGI Open, Hansje talked about ‘Type & Patterns’ in Walhalla Theater, followed by dialogue with Open attendees.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #HansjevanHalem #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @hansjevanhalem

AGI member Peter Biľak established Typotheque type foundry in 1999, co-founded (with Stuart Bailey) Dot Dot Dot journal in 2000, founded magazine Works That Work in 2012 and in 2015 together with Andrej Krátky he co-founded Fontstand.com, a font rental platform. He collaborates with the choreographer Lukas Timulak on creation of modern dance performances. At AGI Open, Peter talked about ‘Dancing Typography’ in Walhalla Kantine.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #peterbilak #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @typotheque @makemovethink

AGI member Lucille Tenazas established Tenazas Design in San Francisco in 1985, working on identity systems and print materials for cultural and non-profit organizations; She has been a design educator for the last twenty years. At AGI Open, Lucille talked about ‘Identity & Anywhere’ in Belvedere Verhalenhuis, followed by dialogue with Open attendees.
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #lucilletenazas #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress

AGI members Fan Ding and Jianping Fang are the founders of design and innovation studio UDL in Beijing (UDL London was established in 2015). Together, they do branding, art direction, photography, spatial design, product design, experience design and editorial design. At AGI Open, Fan and Jianping spoke about ‘Identity & China’ in Belvedere Verhalenhuis.
@udlfangjianping @dingfan_udl #alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress

At AGI Open, AGI member Niels Schrader spoke about Data Pollution in Zaak_Acht, followed by dialogue with Open attendees. Niels - a concept-driven information designer - is the founder of the Amsterdam-based design studio Mind Design and currently, is a member of the advisory panel for the Creative Industries Fund NL. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #NielsSchrader #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress

AGI member Lucienne Roberts is the founder of London-based studio LucienneRoberts+ and the co-founder of publishing house GraphicDesign&. At AGI Open, Lucienne talked about Identity & Activism in Belvedere Verhalenhuis, followed by dialogue with Open attendees. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #lucienneroberts #luciennerobertsplus #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @graphicdesignand_

At AGI Open Rotterdam, German-born graphic designer Jan Wilker (USA, inducted in 2009) gave a talk on Design Business in the Walhalla Kantine. 
Jan moved to New York in late 2000 to start design studio karlssonwilker, together with fellow #AGI member Hjalti Karlsson. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #janwilker @karlssonwilker #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress

Juan Mantilla is the Design Director of Italian cosmetics brand Kiko Milano. At AGI Open, Juan spoke alongside Fedrigoni’s Group Marketing Director Chiara Medioli (who is also the Vice Chair of the Italian paper manufacturer’s Board) about ‘Paper and Plastic’ including environmental considerations in packaging design and innovations in paper. 
#alliancegraphiqueinternationale #AGIOpen #Rotterdam #InProgress @fedrigoni_uk @fedrigonipapers @djfura @kikomilano

If you joined us at last month’s AGI Open festival in Rotterdam, you may have heard from #AGI member Ariane Spanier, whose studio focuses on the design of books, catalogues and posters as well as identities, animations, illustration and digital design. Since 2006, Ariane has been the creative director of Fukt, an annual magazine for contemporary drawing. 
Our media partner magCulture Live recently spoke to Ariane about Fukt for the magCulture Journal and she will be speaking at magCulture Live conference in London on 7 November 2019. 
Grab your ticket using the link in @magculture’s bio to hear from Ariane as well as others in the impressive line-up including Gert Jonkers, Martha Dillon, Serge Ricco, Jody Quon and #AGI member Matt Willey. 
#magculturelive @arianespanier @mrwilley
